work is an exciting new interdisciplinary adventure last quarter's environmental ethics working group kicked off with marilyn cornelius 1st year phd student in the interdisciplinary program in environment and resources iper presenting a paper on global identity and climate justice last quarter's presentations were made by graduate students and post docs in education public policy global justice ethics and society philosophy and iper on topics including national savings and sustainability national obligations to prevent catastrophic climate change how moral and political values affect research the security impacts of climate change who should bear the costs of indian energy policy changes and what drinking water standards are appropriate for rural areas the group meets once a week to discuss a member's research and is funded through woods institute environmental venture project and the program on global justice program debra satz joshua cohen and kenneth arrow serve as faculty advisors aside from eventually publishing the papers the group is organizing a workshop for winter 2009 search fsi search within everything courses events fellowships news op eds people publications research other pages news of interest on stanford radio scott sagan selects the music of ethics and war october 31 2011 cisac fsi stanford in the news new environmental venture grants fsi stanford fse reap in the news the stanford report on june 24 2011 pesd working paper 90 featured in china dialogue's two part article series pesd in the news china dialogue on june 11 2010 michael mcfaul and vladislav surkov to head new working group on civil society cddrl fsi stanford in the news the moscow times on july 20 2009 the international initiative working group program seed beds for new programs & research october 16 2006 news pesd working paper published by global environmental politics march 7 2005 pesd news support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international 